<refnamediv>
<refname>3dtopos</refname>
<refpurpose>produce a &pos; file from a &x3d; file
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<cmdsynopsis>
<command>3dtopos</command>
<arg choice="opt"><option>options</option></arg>
<arg>.3d file</arg>
<arg choice="opt">.3d file</arg>
</cmdsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>
  
<refsect1>
<title>Description</title>

<Para>
3dtopos takes a &x3d; file and produces a &pos; file which contains a
list of all the stations with coordinates (ordered x,y,z [East, North,
Up]) and complete names.
</Para>

<Para>
The stations are sorted such that numbers occur in the correct order
(so ``2'' before ``10'').  3dtopos even sorts numbers with a prefix
and/or suffix, so you'd get:
</Para>

<screen>040.sv8
040.sv8a
040.sv8b
040.sv8c
040.sv9
040.sv10
040.sv11
40_entrance_tag
40b_entrance_tag</screen>

</refsect1>
